    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_es.00711.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>Superintendent's Office</name>
                    <name type="place">Asylum<lb/>for the Insane</name>
                    <name type="place">Ontario</name>
                    <name type="place">London, Ont.,</name>
                    <date when="1890-01-29"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>29 Jan
                        <handShift rend="printed"/>18<handShift rend="manuscript"/>90<ptr target="loc.07337_n1"/></date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>I have a line from Osler<ptr target="n4302"/> this moment. In answer to mine asking
                if they would look after you in Johns Hopkins. I enclose the note. I do not
                understand all of it fully but this much is clear that for about &#36;25. a week (which
                it seems to me we could easily afford) you could be accommodated and provided with
                    <hi rend="underline">every thing</hi>&#8212;of course before taking any step we
                would find out <hi rend="underline">every thing</hi> and I would visit Johns Hopkins
                myself&#8212;I will write again tomorrow when I get Osler's further letter promised
                in this one<ptr target="loc.07337_n2"/></p>
            <closer>
                <signed>R M Bucke</signed>
            </closer>
